items.text: Nice music in the restroom, maybe the dining area can have same music...?
This ps cafe totally rock the ambient is fab. Good place for after work drinks
Love the atmosphere in this place. A definite must try at least once whilst in SG.
Truffle Shoestring Fries and Laksa Leaf Pesto Pasta are must-haves. Don't forget to check out the bar area on level 3 too. Great ambience!
This one of the nicest restaurants/bars in Singapore. Food could be better but it's great for coffee, desserts or drinks.
Cafe has a great ambience and the menu. Great deserts - choice of 10 cakes which are on a display and look delicious. 2 floors and a terrace
Cappuccino here is fantastic
Trainees on job and service is slow.
No pets and kids allowed here.
I go to PS. Cafe for the Double Chocolate Cake. It's heaven in your mouth! But this branch is amazing - spacious, not too casual nor intimidating.
Love the atmosphere!
Per slice of cake is around $14+.. $80 for whole cake.
Order the JOPA!! :)
You need to order truffle fries. Main dish is about $20. Portion is big. Really enjoyed crab tart, pad Thai salad and carrot cake. Laksa pesto was ok. Staff was attentive and super accommodating.
Very romantic setting though they were playing corny pop music that didn't seem to belong. Food portions are huge. Salmon salad was quite good. Burger was ok, not worth the crazy price.
If u said the Truffle flies here is the BEST again, I'm gonna SLAP u really hard! Coz u might as well go bring your own truffle oil! U want Great truffle tries, Go Skinny Pizza!
ambience perfect. service awful. Especially e caucasian waitress who is simple plain rude. NOTE: sign outside also says no kids allowed.

The rooftop is a classic place to take friends, and holds a Thursdays fries & drinks night. The dining area is well laid out, and a pianist sometimes whisks attention away from that last bite of cake.
good for stop by for a drink, good place to read, resting :-) cake is quite big /good to share ^^
Try the Triple-Melted Cheese Toast - too good-- melts in your mouth!
The truffle scramble eggs on croissant is yummy! The truffle fries are huge in portion.
10 points for presentation but was disappointing taste-wise...it made me crave for the Coffee Bean & Tea Leaf version...
The miso cod main course and the sides (salad and roasted pumpkin), and the Poutine are excellent. Trust.
Simply tasty! highly recommended roasted tomato soup and salmon sobu salad for rich taste and fresh ingridients. Lychie sangria & jazzy sound keep you a great company while waiting for the meal!
When you're here, remember to order desserts especially chocolate fudge and apple toffee butterscotch cake! Definitely leaving you wanting for more.
Brunch, salads and desserts
Chocolate Nut Doorstep. YUMMY!!!
this is awesome cafe bar ever! love it!!!
If not for dinner. Stop by for a drink :)
See the fork?
Huge servings, share! And the ambience is really good. Just wondering why is the toilet so cold and with a super big bouquet of flowers covering the mirror .. Haha

Booked for 25 pax, 1 fell sick and couldn't make it, they insisted that we pay for the absentee and when we tried to talk to the manager, his reply is "that's too bad, anyway, I'm very busy right now"
Used to have wonderful, uncomplicated food and an admirable no-kids rule. Have now messed up both so is the same as everywhere else, just more expensive with slightly disappointing food.
The cocktails are very pleasant tho a tad overpriced: vodka cheng tng and the white sangria float my boat
Sticky date pudding!
Big Nihon, PS Digestive Tea & PS Calming Tea are killers! Killer service as well! Check out the toilets and the view from the balcony!
great space, f+*king terrible service.
Truffle fries was pretty norm except that it comes in a huge portion. White Bouquet Sangria was refreshing.
No kids allowed rule!
The Burger is just amazing!!
Perfect ambience for high tea. The turkey cranberry sandwich is yum! Beware of the toilet though, it's cooolllllddd in there!
Great truffle fries for sides ;)
Lemon pudding tastes very Betty Crocker mix. Not worth it.
Great place, good food and nice people!!! Totally recommend
One of the lousiest bar & restaurant. Servers are inattentive. Served desserts without cutleries. Tea without teacups. Have to keep requesting for services. So much for paying a premium.
Nice ambience but tables on 2n level are so cramped up that you dine elbow to elbow with the next person. Slow service. Hopefully this is all due to teething problems.
You have to try their Laksa Pasta.  Cocktail was mediocre.
This is my little happy place. Absolutely fabulous.
Creamy spinach and OZ lamb tenderloin are great!
Nice ambience but the dessert so so...
Delicious pancakes
Very decent, French colonial style influenced place. Good for chilling out after work
The fire shrimp was to die for. Will definitely come back
This is simply going to the best branch of all PS Cafes. Laksa, Eggs Benedict & Fish & Chips. The view from the rooftop is also breathtaking.
They probably have one of the best desserts selection in town. And no kids allowed!
Great place
1) ROOFTOP cafe, in case you're using your GPS. 2) Laksa Pasta is delicious!
awesome environs... bring your date here
Pretty & delicious "white bouquet" cocktail.
Lovely ambience for hearty luncheons.
P.S cafe dinner menu, U SuX! People who return to this place to dine obvious dun appreciate good food. I would have sack the chef from day 1!
Truffle fries, steak sandwich and the salads
Laksa leaf pesto pasta is delicious!
The hot lemon grass tea is soothing :) banana butterscotch cake is not too sweet!
Friendly staff and really excellent food! I recommend this place!
White bouquet sangria is refreshing and subtle
Awesome pls.. Less crowded... Nice place for chilling..
Horrible service every time
Desserts. Drinks. Dainty palates will find dying is, really to a tee, ever so fine.
Dark chocolate banana cheesecake. Oh yes.
I m sure... My bf says he wanna bring me there :-p
Truffle Fries and Sticky Date Pudding are a must in this lovely Café ☺️ Very friendly staff. Nice, cozy ambiance but the smell of bathroom stinks so try to get seats far from the entrance & stairs.
Totally recommend the Sitcky Date for dessert have it with a cup of cafe au lait.
Recommend their dessert "Banana Mango Crumble" perfect blend!
Good food, especially the one on Club Street. All of them have pretty nice ambiance but are uniquely different.
Truffle fries are massive.  Get the salmon and soba salad.  Try gonna kogen beer
Chocolate cake is yummy
The Poutine had mushrooms and shaved parmesan instead of cheese curds and gravy...how wrong was that?
I booked a table for two but it might as well have been for six, as I am so close to the tables either side we have to tuck our elbows in. Not good. Just greedy.
The Pineapple Crumble Cake is horrible. The crumble crust was soft and mushy like mashed potatoes. At $15 a slice it's unacceptable. Our coffees were served at room temp, bad service. Thumbs down
Chocolate cake is the best!!
The place is unique for Singapore - makes you feel like you are in a Hill Station in India !
My fave ps cafe!!!
Sticky date pudding is commendable! Great ambience!
Good lunch spot for business lunches or out-of-town visitors. They don't allow kids so it has a more mature but less jovial vibe than the dempsey location.
No kids allowed. :)
If you want to order the double chocolate cake, make sure you bring at least 4 person! It's damn huge!!
Banana mango crumble is delicious
Pimm's cooler was just the thing for a hot day
land of indulgence it seems :-)
Ginger brûlée a tad too sweet and the swing music a bit too loud, especially when seated in front of speaker! But otherwise, a lovely addition to the PS Cafe chain and a wonderful place for lunch!
Cheese burger always end the Friday nicely.
Great ambience. A tad cramped when its crowded.
Good Caesar salad
My favorite PS, great soup n sandwich for lunch
Absolutely loved this superfood salad. One of the best salads I have ever had with green apple, kiwi & cucumber juice. Great if you want a healthy vegetarian option!
Great spot & amazing view! The truffle Fries are fantastic but the Bolognese Pasta is severely disappointing!
*It's $15++ and $88 ++ A bottle
The cakes are giant and delicious. They also have gluten free cake. While the fries here seem to be famous, I was not that impressed. Great location and décor.
1. The phadthai salad is big on shrimps and vege crunch👍🏼 2. The vegetarian green goddess pasta lives up to its name - Verde, very👍🏼 3. Rickshaw Pork & Crab Noodles - hmm isn't it wanton mee?👎🏼
Stick date pudding was spot on! Perfect with a cup of tea.
Best PS yet ... Could happily lounge every lunchtime away here ...
Great atmosphere for a Sunday brunch. Loved the music on the background. Service was quick and staff was nice. Both PS Pasta and Truffle fries were delicious. Prepare your wallet.
Great food and vibes here, love coming here for both brunch and dinner.
Excellent continental good - try the steaks and Lasagna !
Large portions and comfortable decor kinda justify the high price. Good quality food. Located in a charming converted shophouse. Catch sunset drinks on the top floor where there's a balcony.
Head all the way upstairs for the attic bar and lounge! Delicious cakes that had my mouth watering the second I saw them in the display. Also great staff and service.
Their Truffle Fries are a must try! Not generally affordable, but totally worth it. They serve large proportions and a wide range of menus. They also serve great desserts.
The food is not good at all. Got a sandwich which I could bearly eat as the bread was not fresh. On top, tomato soup had weird bacon taste... Don't think I'd visit any time soon
Quite decent food and nice ambiance. Cake portions are enormous
Atas Food! :)
A great place for Sunday brunch. Try the leftover lasagne
The Chicken Parmigiana was terrific, drink orders take awhile to show up. Still worth the time as overall the meal was wonderful.
The sticky date pudding is to die for. I like to pair that with the lemongrass tea.
Awesome miso cod. Must try.  ^^
Food portion is generous. Try the fries with truffle oil & cheddar cheese.
White sangria #musttry
The truffle french fries is the BEST!!!
what a nice and decent place for fd gathering :)
Chocolate cake!! And nice food!
Try their famous truffle fries! You'll see at least one order of them on each table!
